                            <comment id="13059952" author="gtully" created="Tue, 5 Jul 2011 15:25:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;issue resolved in &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?rev=1143080&amp;amp;view=rev&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?rev=1143080&amp;amp;view=rev&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;stomp disconnect was bypassing delayed shutdown so in the event that a disconnect occurs before a connect is fully formed, the connection was only partially disposed resulting in dangling mbean references.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
